	<text>
		<body>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>Jany 10. 1864</date></p>
				<p>The <sic><addressee>Revd. I Leesor</addressee></sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Herewith I tend the enclosed for publication<lb/> If you <sic>aprove</sic> of the subject&#44; I should like it printed soon.  If it is too great<lb/> a length&#44; I would sooner wait an opportunity&#44; or have <add>it</add> laid on one side rather<lb/> <hi rend="underline">have it continued</hi>&#44; I am now in my 74th year and wish with others to<lb/> put our sentiments on record&#44; to show our <sic>sucessors</sic>&#44; that although living<lb/> in the Centre of the reformers&#44; we are the avowed enemy to <sic>there</sic> Bankrupt<lb/> adventures and their actions.  I have confined myself to facts and if they<lb/> are not ashamed of their <del>open</del> conduct I need neither to be afraid or ashamed to<lb/> publish them.  The article at the <sic>botom</sic> of page no 2. refers to the death<lb/> of <persName>Dr. D I Gans</persName>&#44; the first intemation I had of it was&#44; the <sic>anounce</sic> of his death and<lb/> the funeral service from his late residence &#40;in the <hi rend="underline">Commercial</hi>&#41;</p>
				<p>our Rabbi&#39;s advised this&#44; because he had of late <sic>tenderd</sic> his <add>professional</add> services at<lb/> our Hospital&#44; but <add>for</add> this service he obtained a very considerable practice<lb/> among our own people &#8222;our by laws have assigned a <hi rend="underline">place</hi> in our <sic>cemetry</sic><lb/> for suicides&#8212;and for those marrying out of the pale of Judaism&#44; they<lb/> can have no claim for interment on any account.  I have <sic>carefuly</sic><lb/> read the action of the Board of Delegates and I would prefer&#44; that<lb/> you give it a better Version than I have been able to do.  I hope<lb/> you will be kind enough and correct the errors which are many<lb/> when this is printed please to let my number be accompanied with<lb/> 4 more <sic>copys</sic>.  If the radicals in our midst were as numerous as<lb/> they are wealthy&#44; the Temple scheme would be soon in operation<lb/> still it is hard to say what <del>Gold</del> Gold cannot accomplish</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have collected Material for a continuation <del>of</del> on the Temple<lb/> Mania&#44; and particularly on the subject of seating the sexes<lb/> in the Synagogue which I will forward soon</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">D. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Saml. L. Bruel</persName></p>
		</body>
